transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Jeff Culling. I'm a customer from Scoreblue and I just needed—

Speaker 2: To cancel my prescription. Okay. Let me pull the prescription. Thank you. Mr. Jeffrey Maxson?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir. Houston, Texas?

Speaker 2: Yes. So I see that you have a prescription for Viagra, 50 milligrams from Dr. Wright, 10 tablets. You just don't need a refill or any health concern?

Speaker 1: No, I just don't. I have to cancel my primary care doctor. It's taking me off all ED medications—

Speaker 2: Because of your heart issues?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay. Yeah, it's just the medication change. So unfortunately—

Speaker 1: I have to go off them for a few months.

Speaker 2: Okay. I mean, for a few months, you can put a pause on the prescription. So I can advise the pharmacy to stop the 10 tablets every 30 days and then pause the prescription up to half a year. So if you have the opportunity to return, you don't have to pay a new price. Your old price will be saved.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I'm going to cancel at this time, but I will reach back out to you guys if I ever decide to go back.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah. Just be advised, I'm canceling that doctor prescription. So that being said—

Speaker 1: In the future, either you might have a little bit of an issue reordering, or if you reorder—

Speaker 2: The price will be different because they're going to have to refinance a new doctor to evaluate your medical profile here because that's the only way legally they can provide you Viagra.

Speaker 1: That's what they offer to pause when you go to medical or, you know, any other things—

Speaker 2: They pause you up to half a year and you can reorder and give an update. You know what I mean?

Speaker 1: Oh, yes, sir. I totally understand. I appreciate that information. I just—

Speaker 2: I don't think I'll be going back on it.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah. So I canceled the doctor prescription from Dr. Wright and then I canceled the VIP account and you're all set.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you so much. Have a great day.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: Okay. Take care, sir. Bye.
